news.title: Ahmedabad properties set to get unique address code
news.para: ​The Ahmedabad Municipal Corporation (AMC) is in the advanced stage of inking an MoU with Google to help geotag every property in the city, such that a simple unique alphanumeric digital id will designate these properties to develop a 'Unique Address System' (UAS) for the city - similar to Google's 'Plus codes'.

news.title: Dump construction waste at designated spots: Gurugram civic body commissioner
news.para: ​The MCG officials said that the private firm, which operates Basai plant, can collect C&D waste only within 15 km radius as per their agreement.

news.title: Area, RR rate & construction type may decide property tax amount in Pune
news.para: Presently, the Pune Municipal Corporation (PMC) considers Annual Rateable Value (ARV) as the base price to calculate tax of a property.

news.title: Delhi: Two weeks left, paying property tax online a nightmare
news.para: Many residents complained that their old 15-digit Unique Property Identification Code (UPIC) was not being accepted and they had to register afresh for accessing the portal.

news.title: Noida: Farmhouse owners say their properties are legal & not located on a floodplain
news.para: Owners of these lands maintain that their properties are legal and were registered with due process. They also say that the farmhouses are not located on a “floodplain”, contrary to the Authority’s declaration.

news.title: Gurugram: ATS Kocoon residents forced to cough up double amount for power connection
news.para: Normally, residents of similar societies pay around Rs 6 per unit for DHBVN’s grid supply. ATS Kocoon residents are currently playing around Rs 14 per unit.

news.title: Aggressive capacity expansion by large cement makers may lead to consolidation
news.para: Large manufacturers, such as UltraTech Cement, Ambuja Cements and ACC, have better bargaining power given their scale which helps them achieve lower cost of production compared with smaller rivals. They also tend to have better distribution channels, which helps them improve their market share and capacity utilisation.

news.title: China new home prices fall again in May 2022, more stimulus expected
news.para: Average new-home prices in 70 major cities dropped 0.1% on a month-on-month basis, after a 0.2% decline in April, according to Reuters calculations based on National Bureau of Statistics (NBS) data released on Thursday.

news.title: London: Shaftesbury and Capital & Counties Properties merge in $6 billion deal
news.para: Shaftesbury and Capital & Counties Properties combined property portfolio will comprises about 2.9 million square feet of lettable space in high-profile destinations in London's West End.

news.title: HDFC invokes 50 lakh pledged shares of Ansal Housing for recovery of dues
news.para: Ansal Housing is engaged in the business of construction and development of residential townships and commercial complexes.

news.title: Haryana plans to auction 150-acre land in Gurugram for first phase of global city
news.para: Haryana Chief Minister Manohar Lal Khattar held a series of consultations with developers of NCR, Bangalore and Mumbai to develop a Global City in Gurgaon on 1003 acre land it has identified on Dwarka Expressway.

news.title: Gujarat: Wrong plots auctioned after revenue department's blunder
news.para: The Gujarat high court has not only ordered the land to be restored to the neighbouring village, but also directed the revenue department and Timbdi village panchayat to reallot the residential plots to 76 villagers on another land belonging to Timbdi village.

news.title: Home stays permitted by MTDC need BMC nod: Bombay HC
news.para: Justice Bharati Dangre dismissed an appeal filed by a Juhu resident Harmesh Chadha against a seizure order under section 394 of the BMC Act following an inspection report of the premises by the civic body based on a complaint.

news.title: Navi Mumbai: Cidco gets Rs 865 crore from auction of three Ghansoli plots
news.para: The biggest plot (residential-plus-commercial) of over 16,000 sq m was bagged by Satyam Realty for Rs 1.78 lakh per sq m.

news.title: Kolkata civic body starts drive to raze 50 dilapidated buildings
news.para: The KMC buildings department will need to exercise special power to raze these buildings that pose a threat to those who live in them as well as pedestrians who pass by.
